v OBJECTIVES & ETHOS

The aim of Islamic education lies beyond the borders of this world; it is to gain Paradise in the everlasting life and, ultimately, to learn the pleasure of Allah, the Lord of the Worlds. A College of moral excellence, therefore, is our primary objective where the complete personal development of the student is paramount.

Brondesbury College for Boys offers essential aspects of Arabic and Islamic Studies in conjunction with a broad range of Sciences, Physical Education and National Curriculum disciplines. Motivated by a team of dedicated and professional staff, the education offered at the College aims to produce mature young men with leadership qualities and the ability to contribute, as responsible citizens, to the well being of the pluralistic society as a whole.

The College accepts students from the ages of 11 up to 16, accessible to Muslims regardless of race, colour or status. The emphasis is on providing a healthy all-round education in a positive environment guided by the ethical and moral teachings of Islam.

v FACILITIES

The College comprises two buildings and various annexes which are well equipped with modern facilities and apparatus necessary to teach the National Curriculum up to GCSE. In the main College building, a mosque and assembly hall augments the original classic Georgian building and provides a religious focus and space for daily performance of prayers. The second building is of unique architectural design, and includes a modern well equipped laboratory, art and design lab and a further 3 classrooms, together with a purpose build dining hall. The main building houses two classrooms, a small library and up-to-date Information Technology Centre. The nearby Islamia School Centre provides the College with large gymnasium facilities, and Aylestone playing fields offer boys spacious sports grounds for outdoor activities. Class sizes are kept to a maximum of twenty-four so that as much individual attention as possible can be given to each student. For certain subjects, when appropriate, class numbers may be considerably smaller.

The emphasis is on providing a first-class education in a secure environment where the individual student’s development is regularly monitored and assessed. The comprehensive curriculum will prepare our students thoroughly for admission to further education institutions.

v NATIONAL CURRICULUM SUBJECTS

The emphasis is on providing a first class education in a secure environment where the individual student's development is regularly monitored and assessed. The comprehensive curriculum will thoroughly prepare our students For higher or further education institutions.

The College’s Key Stage 3 curriculum (Years 7 to 9) is as follows:

v English

v Mathematics

v Science

v ICT

v Islamic Studies

v Arabic

v Quranic Studies

v French (Year 7)

v History

v Art and Design (including calligraphy)

v Physical Education

v Citizenship

The College offers the following subjects at GCSE:

v Arabic

v Islamic Studies

v Biology

v Physics

v Chemistry

v English Language

v English Literature

v Mathematics

v Information Technology

v Physical Education

v Citizenship

The following are also available as optional subjects:

v Business Studies

v History

v Art and Design

v PASTORAL AND SOCIAL CARE

In their first year at College students will be assigned a Form Tutor who will meet students on a regular basis so that individual strengths or weaknesses can be quickly recognised. He will keep a close eye on academic progress, identifying any problems early on and give constant advice and encouragement. The Vice-Principal is also available to counsel students on an individual basis.


Half way through each term, interim reports are discussed with each student by the subject and form teachers. A full behavioural and academic report is sent to parents twice a year (December and July) with two brief mid-term reports (October and April). Additionally, formal parents evening are arranged in the year to discuss students’ progress with subject and form teachers. Parents are also welcome to arrange an appointment to discuss the progress of their children when it is felt necessary to do so. An external testing and target setting programme is also in place to ensure rigorous monitoring of the academic progress of our students.

v HOME STUDY

Homework and study is an integral and essential aspect of the curriculum and of student life in general as it enhances the attainment and progress of the student. Students will be required to do homework/study every evening and complete occasional projects in the holidays. An approximate indication of expectations is given below:

Year 7: 45-90 minutes per day

Year 8: 60-90 minutes per day

Year 9: 90-120 minutes per day

Year 10: 120-150 minutes per day

Year 11: 150-180 minutes per day

The homework is in accordance with our College homework policy and Home-School Agreement which parents and students must sign upon acceptance of an offer of a place at the College.

v THE SCHOOL CALENDAR

The academic year is divided into three terms in line with standard English terms and runs from September through to July. Precise dates will be available at the start of each academic year, but a general indication of term times is as follows:

Autumn – early September to mid-December

Spring – early January to late March/early April

Summer – mid-April to mid-July

The College also incorporates a specially suited calendar of Islamic months: the last 10 days of Ramadhan, the first 10 days of Dhul Hijja and the two Eids are normally taken as holidays and for religious observances. There are normally half-term holidays of approximately one week in the middle of each term.

v THE SCHOOL DAY

The school day begins at 8.30 am with registration and assembly and end at 3.30 pm. There are five periods during the day (of 60 minutes duration). The breakdown of the school day is shown below:

Monday-Thursday

8:30 am: Registration

8:40 am: Assembly

8:50 am: Period 1

9:50 am: Period 2

10:50 am: Break

11:10 am: Period 3

12:10 pm: Period 4

1:10 pm: Lunch

2:00 pm: Zuhr Prayer

2:15 pm: Period 5

3:15 pm: Tutorial Session

3:30 pm: End of School Day

Friday

8:30 am: Registration

8:40 am: Assembly

8:50 am: Period 1

9:50 am: Period 2

10:50 am: Break

11:10 am: Period 3

12:10 pm: Period 4

1:10 pm: Lunch

2:00 pm: Khutba & Juma Prayer

2:30 pm: Period 5

3:30 pm: End of School Day

v CATERING

The College employs Muslim caterers to provide nutritious and balanced lunches strictly complying with Islamic requirements for the College’s students. Light refreshments can also be purchased during break periods from the College’s ‘Tuck Shop’.

v ENROLMENT

Applications are welcome from all members of the community. All applicants have to sit entrance examinations in English (literacy, including verbal reasoning), mathematics (numeracy) and basic Islamic Studies. It should be noted that the College is an independent institution and fees are payable by all parents. The current annual fee is £6100.

v CAREERS EDUCATION

As part of their preparation for the future, the College puts an emphasis on careers education from Year 9 onwards. All students are regularly interviewed and advised in order to assist them in their choice of career and eventually, university. Work experience placements are arranged for the College’s Year 10 students for two weeks each year. Year 10 also partake in the Young Enterprise business project and the excellent Duke of Edinburgh Award which we link up with GCSE Citizenship Studies.

v MANAGEMENT

The College recognises the importance of cooperation between school and parents. With this in mind the Shura, the College’s management committee, has two parent members, elected by ballot each year, together with teacher representatives, Principal of the College and the Chairman/Vice-Chairperson of Waqf-al-Birr Trust.

Top Page


v OBJECTIVES & ETHOS

The aim of Islamic education lies beyond the borders of this world; it is to gain Paradise in the everlasting life and, ultimately, to learn the pleasure of Allah, the Lord of the Worlds. A College of moral excellence, therefore, is our primary objective where the complete personal development of the student is paramount.

Brondesbury College for Boys offers essential aspects of Arabic and Islamic Studies in conjunction with a broad range of Sciences, Physical Education and National Curriculum disciplines. Motivated by a team of dedicated and professional staff, the education offered at the College aims to produce mature young men with leadership qualities and the ability to contribute, as responsible citizens, to the well being of the pluralistic society as a whole.

The College accepts students from the ages of 11 up to 16, accessible to Muslims regardless of race, colour or status. The emphasis is on providing a healthy all-round education in a positive environment guided by the ethical and moral teachings of Islam.

The Antares Ship Yards are Federation shipyards presumably located in the Bajor sector. The USS Enterprise (NCC-1701-B) was constructed at the Antares Ship Yards prior to its launch from Earth orbit in 2293.

The class prototype USS Defiant was launched from the Antares yards on stardate 47538.5, and the USS Valiant was launched on stardate 49456.5.


[edit] Great Cockcrow Railway

After the death of Sir John Samuel, who had founded the Greywood Central Railway in 1946 at a private address in Walton-on-Thames, the publisher Ian Allan purchased everything and in 1968 created the Great Cockcrow Railway in Lyne near Chertsey. Since then, the GCR has grown to 5 miles in length and demonstrates 1950s prototypical British signalling methods.

[edit] [Empire of Ularis]

Ularis is a nation in the world of Nationstates. Ularis is the new UN delegate for its region United Kingdom of Dragonstone.

[edit] Sources

Natonstates.net

Location: United Kingdom of Dragonstone Regional Influence: Powerbroker


The Empire of Ularis is a very large, safe nation, notable for its compulsory military service. Its compassionate, hard-working, cynical population of 126 million are ruled by a mostly-benevolent dictator, who grants the populace the freedom to live their own lives but watches carefully for anyone to slip up.

It is difficult to tell where the omnipresent, corrupt government stops and the rest of society begins, but it juggles the competing demands of Law & Order, Defence, and the Environment. The average income tax rate is 72%, and even higher for the wealthy. Private enterprise is illegal, but for those in the know there is a slick and highly efficient black market in Gambling.

The wearing and manufacture of fur apparel is banned, a spate of enforced closures has left 'Government FM' as the nation's only radio station, the poor are often seen pale and dizzy after selling their blood to make ends meet, and anti-environmentalist protesters are gunned down without mercy. Crime -- especially youth-related -- is totally unknown, thanks to the all-pervasive police force and progressive social policies in education and welfare. Ularis's national animal is the Pyrodragon, which frolics freely in the nation's many lush forests, and its currency is the DragonBond.

Ularis is ranked 9th in the region and 85,900th in the world for Largest Insurance Industry.

[edit] Sources

lalala

William Henry Gates III (born October 28, 1955) is the co-founder, chairman, and chief software architect of Microsoft Corporation, the world's largest software company (as of April 2006). He is also the founder of Corbis, a digital image archiving company. Forbes international rich list has ranked him as the world's richest person for the last twelve straight years. In 1999, Gates' wealth briefly surpassed $100 billion, making him the world's first centibillionaire. When family wealth is considered, his family ranks second behind the Walton family.[3][4]

Gates is one of the best-known entrepreneurs of the personal computer revolution. He is widely respected for his intelligence, foresight, and ambition. He is also widely criticized as having built Microsoft's business through unfair, illegal, or anticompetitive business practices. Government authorities in several countries have found some of Microsoft's practices illegal, as in United States v. Microsoft.

Since amassing his fortune, Gates has pursued a number of philanthropic endeavors, donating large amounts of money (about 51% of his total fortune) to various charitable organizations and scientific research programs through the Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation, founded in 2000. He, his wife Melinda and U2's lead singer Bono were collectively named by Time as the 2005 Persons of the Year. That same year he was given an honorary Knight Commander of the Order of the British Empire by Queen Elizabeth II. In 2006, Gates Foundation was awarded the Premio Príncipe de Asturias en Cooperación Internacional.

[edit] Bill Smith (Diver)

Bill Smith began diving for pleasure off the River Tyne on the North East coast of england in 1986. Due to the Tyne's importance as a coaling port and shipbuilding / repair facility for centuries the seabed surrounding the river mouth is littered with wrecks. Not being satisfied with diving the better known sites bill rapidly acquired the necessary skills and equipment to locate more difficult targets. Having developed techniques to accurately locate small objects in deep water these techniques were most publicly demonstrated during the project to recover the remains of Donald Campbell and his jet hydroplane, Bluebird. This was closely followed by the same team positively locating the minefield that sank Titanic's sister ship, Britannic in the Kea Channel off Greece. Bill continues to be actively involved with police underwater search units and equipment manufacturers to further develop the lessons learned and has participated in several recoevries of missing persons as well as a high-profile murder investigation for which the team gathered crucial evidence.

Lee Dixon, the former England and Arsenal soccer star is a major shareholder and Non - Exec director of NeonHippo.

[edit] Stuart A. Paterson

Poet, born 1966, Truro, raised in Ayrshire, Scotland. Volumes of poetry - Mulaney of Larne & Other Poems (University of Leiden 1991)
Saving Graces (Diehard Press, Scotland 1997) as well as work in Dream State; The New Scottish Poets (Polygon 1994, 2002), The Forward Book of Poetry 1994, A Year in Poetry (Crown Publishing 1995), Scottish Literature in the 20th Century, ed. McCordick (Scottish Cultural Press 2002) & many others. Poetry in various magazines/newspapers including New Writing Scotland, Chapman, The Scotsman, The Herald, The New Welsh Review, Poetry Scotland, Lines Review, Envoi, New Contrast South African Literary Journal & others. Founder/editor of Spectrum, international poetry & prose review, 1989-96 Founder of Kilmarnock North-West Writers' Group 1991. Winner of an Eric Gregory Award, UK Society of Authors, 1992. Recipient of a Scottish arts Council Writer's Bursary 1993. SAC/DGAA Dumfries & Galloway Writing Fellow 1996-98. URL Homepage - http://www.myspace.com/unclestoosh

[edit] Thirunaalaippovaar Nayanar

Nandhanar, came from SC/ST caste (not brahman by birth). In olden days people from SC/ST are not alowed to enter Temples, but they can worship from outside. Daily, Nandhanar use to sincerely worship lord Siva from outside, but still Lord nandhiyamperuman will always sit infront of the Lord Shiva. Thus hiding the Lord Shiva. So no one can see Shiva straight by directly standing from outside the temple. But due to his sincere worship and love towards Lord Shiva, The God ordered Lord Nandhiyamperuman to move a little so that Nandhanar can view him directly. This is depicted in a temple in Thripongur (near Chidambaram). For many years he had a big interest for worshiping Siva in Main Temple in Chidambaram. But as usualy no one allowed him. At a moment an echo (obviously of Siva) stating that to drop Nandhanar in fire. So all Iyer/Gurukal did the same. After dropping him Nandhanar came again in golden colour with moopori poonool. Then he became a Brahman and now he entered the temple and mixed (attained moksham) with the holy sprit of Lord Shiva

[edit] The British Conservative Catholics

The British Conservative Catholics was a spoof website created by Tobias Depson, and featuring various members of the Depson family as founder members. The earliest entry for the British Conservative Catholic website on the wayback machine is June 05 2001. The last being February 05 2005. It is thought the site finally went offline in late 2004.

The British Conservative Catholic website featured a hardline catholic organisation, that among other things condememned Brad Pitt as 'satanic', David Bowie for creating homosexuality, and featured various other xenophobic articles that were ludicrously right wing, and yet strangely believable.

The website also featured highly in the press, with their articles about Marilyn Manson appearing in Metal Hammer magazine.

Various members of the Depson family featured in the organisation. Deborah Depson offered hardline catholic advice to spoofed letters sent into the site. In one letter she encourages a wife to purchase an anti-erection ring to stop her husband from msturbating and in another condemns a womans daughter for dating a negro. Martin O' Connel is supposedly the founder member, with press and IT sectors being headed by Tobias and Deborah Depson in charge of administration. Gavin Depson supposedly has the rather difficult task of legal advisor.

The arch enemies of the BCC is the secretive Atheist Movement, which though not publicly known, is purportedly a wide netowrk aimed at limiting the BCC's power and infusing atheism into the public.

In addition to the articles and advice on the website, the BCC also had an online store, that featured products such as anti masturbation equipment, and books with provocative titles including Mein Kampf for children, the bible for women, and bullying tips for catholic children.

The BCC website eventually went down as it's hosting provider would no longer support the site. However there are various other ideas circulating around forums on the internet with regards to it's demise. Tobias himself offered full rights to the site to anyone emailing asking if they could provide hosting to replace it. It perhaps therefore can be speculated that Tobias simply got bored with the spoof after 3 years of posing as hardline right wing catholic extremist.

[edit] Barthco International, Inc.

Barthco International, Inc. is a successor to John H. Faunce Co., Inc., established in 1908 as a customs brokerage and freight forwarding firm. Barthco International was founded in 1968 and has grown and changed alongside the complex world of international business, becoming one of the largest privately-held logistic organizations in the United States.

The guiding principle on which Barthco was established is to assess problem areas affecting international business and provide accurate and timely solutions. Following this strategy, Barthco has been able to anticipate and identify potential problems before they became major client obstacles. Today, over 30 years later, Barthco continues to stand by this belief and has grown into a leading full-service international logistics company.

Barthco International, Inc is among the top five Customs Brokers in the United States in terms of number of entries processed according to U.S. Department of the Treasury statistics. Barthco International has a fully staffed Bond and Insurance Department ready to offer competitive rates and quality service.Barthco is a Marine/Air Cargo Insurance company, providing quality insurance services at affordable prices.Barthco International offers comprehensive freight forwarding services, to and from any point in the world as well as warehousing and distribution solutions. Barthco Trade Consultants was formed to provide importers and exporters with needed services above and beyond traditional customs brokerage and forwarding.

Since Barthco was already involved with cargo security legislation pre-September, it is in position to provide its expertise to the federal government post-September. Barthco's involvement in the Border Security Advisory Group to the Commercial Operations Advisory Committee of the U.S. Treasury Department contributed to the formulation of enhanced security programs to maintain the level of logistics integrity that will facilitate safe global commerce while protecting U.S. borders from terrorist attack.

[edit] Magnus Opus The Movie

Magnus Opus The Movie is a hilarious mockumentary about a esoteric performance artist named Magnus and his mission to inspire the world with his occultish brand of "internal deconstructive expressionism". [edit] Halliford School

Halliford School is a small independant school for boy's in Shepperton, Near London, England. The School Was founded in the 1930's and moved to its current location in the 18'th century Halliford House in the 1940's. Since then the school has constantly been expanding and now has several modern classroom blocks, a modern theater and a new sports hall opened by England coach Andy Robinson in 2006. The school takes Boys from ages 11-18 and girls from ages 16-18.

172.216.126.81 18:17, 19 May 2006 (UTC)

In the United States Navy, the 3rd Fleet is the fleet responsible for naval activities in the eastern and northern Pacific Ocean. It is headquartered on USS Coronado. The 3rd Fleet was initially formed on March 15, 1943 under the command of Admiral William F. Halsey, and was responsible for much of the campaigning in the Pacific theater in World War II. The fleet was put into reserve on October 7, 1945. It was reactivated February 1, 1973 at Ford Island in Pearl Harbor as part of a Pacific Fleet reorganization. 3rd Fleet took over the duties of U.S. 1st Fleet and the Pacific Anti-Submarine Warfare Force.

Third Fleet was originally formed during World War II on March 15, 1943 under the command of Admiral William F. “Bull” Halsey. He opened his headquarters ashore in Pearl Harbor, territory of Hawaii, on June 15, 1944. The fleet operated in and around the Solomon Islands, the Philippines, Formosa, Okinawa and the Ryukyu Islands. It also operated in Japanese waters launching attacks on Tokyo, the naval base at Kure and the island of Hokkaido.

Embarked aboard his flagship, USS Missouri, Admiral Halsey led his fleet into Tokyo Bay on August 29, 1945. On September 2, surrender documents ending the war were signed on her decks. Third Fleet remained in Japanese waters until late September when its ships were directed to sail for the West Coast of the United States. On October 7, 1945 Third Fleet was designated a reserve fleet and decommissioned from active status. On February 1, 1973, following a reorganization of the Pacific Fleet, the United States Third Fleet was recommissioned as an active fleet and assumed the duties of the former First Fleet and Pacific Anti-Submarine Warfare Force located at Ford Island, Hawaii. Third Fleet trains naval forces for overseas deployment and evaluates state-of-the-art technology for fleet use. Additionally, Third Fleet could deploy in the event of a major conflict.

On November 26, 1986, Commander, Third Fleet shifted his flag from his headquarters ashore to resume status as an afloat commander for the first time since World War II, aboard USS Coronado (AGF 11). In August 1991, Third Fleet’s commander, his staff and the command ship, USS Coronado, shifted homeports to San Diego, California. In September, 2003, Commander, Third Fleet shifted his flag from the command ship USS Coronado to headquarters ashore at Point Loma, San Diego, California.

<source http://www.3rdfleet.16.forumer.com

[edit] Al Emmo and the Lost Dutchman's Mine

Al Emmo and the Lost Dutchman's Mine is an adventure game for the PC which is currently undergoing development by the company "Himalaya Studios". Little is known about the game, other than it is based around the misfortunes of a feeble, middle-aged, balding dork who has recently arrived in the desert town of Anozira. Al is searching for a suitable bride to bring home and impress his parents. Things do not go exactly as planned, and Al soon finds himself seeking the treasures of a long lost gold mine instead.

The game contains slapstick humor and is rumoured to be a comedy of errors, with many of the jokes stemming from the omnipresent God-like narrator poking fun of Al and his bumbling ways.

The game is expected to be somewhat similar in style to the Leisure Suit Larry series.

[edit] Pierre DuMaine

Bishop Pierre DuMaine served as bishop for the first 18 years of the Diocese of San Jose. He was born in Paducah, Kentucky on August 2, 1931. Educated in Catholic schools in Paducah and California, he attended St. Joseph College, Mountain View, and St. Patrick Seminary in Menlo Park. Bishop DuMaine was ordained a priest of the Archdiocese of San Francisco on June 15, 1957. He earned his doctorate in education at the Catholic University of America in 1961 where he served as Assistant Professor until 1963. From 1963 through 1965 Bishop DuMaine taught at Serra High School. He then served as Assistant Superintendent and Superintendent of Schools for the Archdiocese of San Francisco from 1965-78. Bishop DuMaine was named Prelate of Honor on July 18, 1972. He was ordained bishop in San Francisco on June 29, 1978. He was founding Director of Catholic Television Network in Menlo Park from 1978-1981. On January 27, 1981, Bishop DuMaine was named by Pope John Paul to be the first bishop of the new Diocese of San Jose where he was installed officially on March 18, 1981. His request to retire was accepted by the Holy Father on November 27, 1999.

Since retirement Bishop DuMaine has remained active in national Bishops’ Committees for Science and Human Values and for Women in Society and the Church. He has participated in dialogues and conferences on Science and Religion, and has taught in Religious Studies Departments of Stanford University and Santa Clara University. Santa Clara has appointed him Presidential Professor of Catholic Theology.

[edit] Lanny Frattare

Lanny Frattare has been associated with Pittsburgh Pirate radio and television broadcasts long enough to be remembered in the same light with former game-callers Bob Prince and Rosey Rosewell. He has worked alongside long time Houston Astros announcer Milo Hamilton. He has also worked with former All-Star pitchers and current broadcasters Steve Blass and Bob Walk. He also currently works alongside former Buffalo Bison broadcaster Greg Brown and former utility infielder and former Altoona Curve manager John Wehner doing the broadcasts for KDKA-AM 1020, Fox Sports Pittsburgh TV and across numerous affilites in Pennsylvania, Florida, Ohio and West Virginia.

[edit] Sources

The 2006 season marks Lanny Frattare's 31st as a radio/TV broadcaster with the Pirates. With over 30 years behind the microphone, no other person has brought the action to Bucco fans longer than Lanny.

A native of Rochester, NY, Frattare received his bachelor's degree in communications from Ithaca (NY) College in 1970. He joined the Pirates behind the microphone at the major league level in 1976.

In October of 2006, Lanny will host the 20th annual Family Links Golf Classic. Over the past two decades, Lanny and his friends have raised over $1.6 million in support of over 32,000 children, families and mentally challenged individuals served yearly by the Family Links staff.

Frattare's wife, Christine, is a music teacher in the Upper St. Clair school district and serves as the Music Director of Westminster Presbyterian Church in Upper St. Clair. She is also the conductor of the Junior Mendelssohn Choir of Pittsburgh.

Lanny has two children; son David (31) and daughter Megan (24). David currently works in the Attorney General's office of the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania. David and his wife, Ann Marie, are the proud parents of two children; son Spencer (4) and daughter Carly (2). Megan is currently residing in Philadelphia.

[9]

69.171.25.22 19:19, 19 May 2006 (UTC)James W. Banks - Niagara Falls, NY.

[edit] [Post Mortem]

"Post Mortem": Play by Noel Coward.

"Post Mortem" is what can only be described as a dramatic study of war and its effects. It follows the story of soldier John Cavan who, in the moment of his death, is given the opportunity to see what the future holds for those he is leaving behind. Published in "Play Parade, Volume One", in the introduction the author claims that it was more his thoughts placed on paper rather than a play written to be performed, but nonetheless it posesses certain aspects which some might say would make an interesting and challending performance, and offers a wide range of characters and situations. It was published in 1934 with an introduction by Noel Coward saying that it "might probably be quite effective," (should it be performed)"provided that it is expertly directed and acted".


[edit] Sources

"Play Parade, Volume One, by Noel Coward".

[edit] Ultimate Spiderman Annual

In 2005, Marvel Comics published a line of Ultimate Annuals which told a side story that would later be of importance to the main storyline. These titles were Ultimate spiderman, Ultimate x-men, Ultimate Fantastic Four and The Ultimates. In August of this year [2006] another line of Ultimate Annuals are said to be published.


Bold text Ultimate Spiderman Annual #1

Written by Brian Michael Bendis, the writer of all 94 current issues of Ultimate Spiderman, continues the run by also writing the Annual. He is also joined by Mark Bagley who did the cover.

This issue focus' on the start of the Peter Parker-Kitty Pryde relationship. This plays a significant part in the upcoming issues of Ultimate Spiderman.

The story starts in the Xavier mansion, with Nightcrawler, Colossus and Kitty Pryde, from the X-men, in the danger room. The scene is from the Lord of the Rings with the three mutants fighting a dragon. Kitty leaves feeling down.

We then cut to Spiderman fighting the huge Rhino. As things look bad for Spidey, the army shows up. While destracted, Spiderman then pounces on Rhino and breaks open what appears to be his power source. After piercing the source with a wooden stick, the Rhino falls to the floor. Spidey is then confronted by who appears to be general Ross, yet Spidey quickly swings away.

Back at the Xavier mansion, it becomes clear why Kitty is so down, she misses Bobby a.k.a Iceman. After storming off in a huff, Jean Grey confronts her to see what is wrong. After reading her thoughts, Jean realises kitty finds Spiderman attractive. She decides to call him.

Peter picks up his ringing phone, yet Kitty hangs up. She tries again and prevails. After an embarrassing moment, a date is finally arranged.

They meet at Peters school and then head for the mall. They talk about their own lives and an uncomfortable conversation about Iceman comes up. it is abrupted by Flash Thompson throwing a drink at Peters face.

They escape to the roof where they are about to share a romantic kiss, when an explosion is heard. It is coming from Shocker. They easily aprahend him and swing away back to the rooftop. A kiss is finally shared, yet Kitty is then lifted back into the X-men's aircraft.

[edit] Gamblers (breakdancing)

The Gamblers crew of Korea have become well-known for their amazing performances in Battle of the Year (BOTY) competitions and often featured in internet videos across the web due to their high level of talent. What probably makes them so well-known and loved is the fact that each of the bboys in the crew have their own unique ability used for the good of the whole team, instead of each having generic breakdancing skills like a lot of other crews.

For example, Bboy Bruce Lee and Bboy The End (aka KYS) are skilled powerheads; Bboy Lazer is a master headspinner, often considered one of the best bboys out there at headspinning; Soul Soy focuses on footwork and style; Bboy Sick has a unique contortionist style of bending his body in very flexible positions while he dances across the floor; Bboy Darkness is widely considered one of the best bboys at doing freezes such as handstands and airchairs--often compared to France's own Bboy Junior. The list of the crew's individual talents goes on and on, due to the fact that more and more members seem to be popping up!

The crew have currently opened up a breakdancing school in South Korea and are becoming more and more popular by the day. Bboy Darkness, also caled "The One", is credited for making most of the videos and photographs of the group for promotional purposes. It is said that without his dedication to his crew, Gamblers wouldn't be as popular as they are today.

[edit] Lindsay Ballard

Lindsay Ballard was born May 7th, 1986 in Wichita, KS. She was immediately given away for adoption due to her love of the hated sudoku and making everything awkward. She was eventually shipped overseas and was adopted by a viking family in Hungary. Lindsay was very bitter about be given up for adoption. She decided to get back at her family by becoming the best Horseshoe Player in the history of the game (some say Hungary was actually the original site of Horseshoes). Ballard quickly became the best horseshoe player ever. Mainly because there are only about 6 people in the world that play horseshoes. After dominating the game for several years she moved on to puzzles. Lindsay Ballard loves puzzles. She is desperately looking for heated competitions for solving puzzles which include Sudoku, Word Search, Chicktionary, Crosswords, Cryptoquip, and long division problems.

Lindsay Ballard moved back to Wichita in the late '90s and really tore up the puzzle scene, but she remained true to her roots and made everybody feel awkward. She graduated from Bishop Carroll in 2004 after reuniting with her parents. Once her parents saw how amazing she was at horseshoes and UNO (see next paragraph) they decided they could look past all the awkwardness and reading, and puzzles.

Today Lindsay Ballard attends KU and plays UNO. In April she was declared best uno player ever. It is said that she wins roughly 73% of the games she plays. The amazing thing about her uno skills is she doesn't even like UNO, she plays to kill time while at work. She does enjoy her job but not her co-workers. Ballard cringes at the site of them. Ballard works at INTRUST Bank where she is a lead teller.

Random Facts about Ballard: She is powered by Dr. Pepper. She has a "SUDOKU RULEZ" tattoo and her shoulder blade. Her favorite activity (besides puzzles) is climbing trees. Ballard despises dogs.

[edit] Bukark

The word Bukark was originally a word for chicken and was the founding basis for the website network known as Bukark-u-later, initially created in 2002, later disbanded in 2004. The site was a general entertainment site and the company using the name 'Bukark-u-later' created a wide selection of games for the PC, many of which were available for free download. It went on to be known simply as 'U-Later' for a few months but this later disbanded also.

[edit] rapt clothing

Rapt clothing came about as a result of two individuals’ desire to provide people with quality clothing and designs that are rooted in the unconventional. We stand in solidarity with social, political, cultural and spiritual consciousness: one which is neither bold nor underlined, but rather figurative. 2005 is the birth year for the small company with sound ambitions. We will proudly strive to produce pieces that are multi-leveled and ever changing. Funk and class, the powerful and the subtle, the serious and the fun meet on the crossroads called Rapt.
The word “rapt” means to be absorbed or captivated by an event or a moment. We find ourselves constantly seeking aesthetic moments in life that evoke overwhelming emotions, move us in an incomprehensible fashion, and challenge our sense of self. It is the texture of these experiences that inspire our designs. We invite you to view our 2005 collection, hoping that you might become rapt yourselves.

[edit] Riverside High School (El Paso, Texas)

Riverside High School is a public four-year traditional high-school in El Paso's Ysleta Independent School District. The school serves several neighborhoods in El Paso's Lower Valley (sometimes called the Mission Valley). The school opened in 1968 and had its first graduating class in 1973. A 4A school, Riverside has about 1,400 students, most of whom are Mexican-American.

Riverside has a magnet program called the Socratic Institute that caters to students interested in pursuing a career in pedagogy. Riverside is also home to the district's Academy of Science and Technology. The school also began the now defunct CyberInstitute that catered to students interested in computer information. The Ysleta school district is currently studying the idea of creating a law enforcement magnet program. Riverside has had a long history of academic success. At one point, the school was the public high school sending the most Hispanic students to Ivy League universities. Riverside graduates are often accepted to other top universities like Stanford, MIT, Rice and the top public universities in the state of Texas.

Athletically, the Riverside Rangers have arguably given the city of El Paso the most media recognition in prep sports in the last 20 years. The basketball and baseball teams have reached the Final Four in the state tournament (the only teams in the city to achieve this feat recently) and the football team is the only El Paso team to reach the state regional semi-finals two straight years. The varsity football team has not lost a district game in six years and has qualified for the playoffs every year for more than a decade.

Riverside has also had top music programs, dance teams, cheeerleading squads and forensic teams.

[edit] Lifewaltz

Lifewaltz is a webcomic written by Richard McCann and Rob Mitchell, who more commonly refer to themselves as Rico and Mitch, respectively. Production of these comics is inconsistent, writers aim to get a new one up every monday. Officially, Lifewaltz has been going since 2005, but the original comics started a few years earlier, albeit with a slightly different team.

The comics follow two characters pretty much based on the writers. Their adventures are often confined to their house, and despite a surreal tendency, are often based on real life events or circumstances Rico and Mitch find themselves in.

[edit] Multiple Integrals Outline

1) The Concept - With Normal integrals, we are trying to find an area under a curve. With double integrals, we are trying to find a volume under a curve, within a rectangle R. We have dA, which is the product of dx and dy, and a height z, which varies with dx and dy. The more integrals we have, the more dimensions we deal with. Needless to say, the concept begins to grow more complex at the third integral. (5-10 mins?)

2) Real-life Applications - Can be used to calculate

Center of mass of objects with uneven density
Average snowfall over a state

Use your imagination (and the textbook) here. (5 mins)

3) Solving a simple multiple integral equation: Show how one solves a simple equation, then present another problem for the class to solve (then solve it...). (15-20 mins)

4) Describe tricks and techniques to solve more difficult equations (optional - 5, 10 minutes)

[edit] Lifewaltz

Lifewaltz is a webcomic written by Richard McCann and Rob Mitchell, who more commonly refer to themselves as Rico and Mitch, respectively. Production of these comics is inconsistent, writers aim to get a new one up every monday. Officially, Lifewaltz has been going since 2005, but the original comics started a few years earlier, albeit with a slightly different team.

The comics follow two characters pretty much based on the writers. Their adventures are often confined to their house, and despite a surreal tendency, are often based on real life events or circumstances Rico and Mitch find themselves in.


[edit] The Comics

Sometimes Lifewaltz follows a story arc, but this is usually interrupted by a more random issue that breaks away from the chain of events or is a simple one-off gag (such as the parody of the iPod commercial, arbitarily inserted into the Monkey Paintball story, or a piece of fan work). The writers have expressed their dislike for these story arcs. Each strip also includes commentaries from the authors, although Mitch's comments box is, more often than not, empty. Fans of the series will note that this reflects the inherent laziness of his character.

They also make numerous references to their favourite video games, films, comics, books, television shows and technologies.

[edit] Tanya Remenikova

Tanya Remenikova is a Russian-American cellist who has performed extensively in the United States, Europe, and Russia. Her performances have been praised in the New York Times for their "exceptional zest and songful strength" and "rich baritonal color." Remenikova was the top prize winner at the 1969 Cassado Competition in Florence, Italy. She studied with Valentin Berlinsky of the Borodin Quartet and with Mstislav Rostropovich at the Moscow Conservatory, where she later served as his teaching assistant. She and her husband, pianist Alexander Braginsky, left the Soviet Union in 1972 before becoming artists-in-residence at Cambridge University in the United Kingdom. She was appointed to the faculty of the University of Minnesota in 1976 where she continues to teach and perform. She has recorded for the DDR and Sound Star Tone labels and inspired a set of pieces for solo cello by Judith Zaimont named "Tanya - Three Poems for Cello." Her students serve as pricipals of major orchestras and professors at universities throughout the United States and the world.

[edit] Sean McCormack

Assistant Secretary of State, US

Sean McCormack was sworn in as Assistant Secretary for Public Affairs and Department Spokesman on June 2, 2005. Immediately prior to returning to the State Department, Mr. McCormack served as Special Assistant to the President, Spokesman for the National Security Council, and Deputy White House Press Secretary for Foreign Policy.

Mr. McCormack began his career in the Foreign Service in 1995. He served at the U.S. embassy in Ankara from 1996 to 1998, where he was assigned as the Farsi-speaking officer in the consular section. He was posted to the U.S. embassy in Algiers from 1998 to 1999, with responsibility for economic reporting and consular issues. Mr. McCormack served in the State Department Operations Center in 1999 before moving to the Executive Secretariat Staff ("The Line"). He was detailed to the National Security Council Staff in 2001.

Prior to joining the Foreign Service, Mr. McCormack was an analyst at the Meridian Corporation working on issues related to arms control and non-proliferation.

Mr. McCormack graduated from Colby College in 1986 with a Bachelor’s degree in economics. He received an M.A. in international relations from the University of Maryland, College Park in 1990

[edit] Sepermeru

Sepermeru was the religious capital of the 19th Nome of Upper Egypt, located on an irrigation canal near the general entrance to the Fayuum Oasis. This outpost settlement was situated roughly mid-way between Oxyrhynchos (Per Medjed) to the south and Herakleopolis to the north. According to ancient taxation records and other pertinent sources, Sepermeru was a noted settlement for active and retired military personnel and their familes, particularly during the New Kingdom reign of the Rameses pharaohs. Agriculture was also practiced here. The chief deities of the town were the god Set and the goddess Nephthys; both of these deities were highly favored by the war-like Ramessid Dynasty of kings for their ominous, agrressive attributes. As revealed by ongoing excavations in the 1980s, two provincial temples were built in Sepermeru, existing from (at least) the 19th and 20th Dynastic periods. One temple was dedicated to Set while the other temple enclosure belonged to Nephthys. Separate, hierarchical priesthoods for both deities are named, for taxation purposes, in the Wilbour Papyrus: two "prophets" of "Set of Sepermeru" and two "prophets" and a "wa'ab" priest in the service of "Nephthys of Sepermeru" (19th and 20th Dynasties). In all likelihood, the temples were either built or considerably refurbished by Rameses III. Only the foundation stones of both temples remain today and, by Ptolemaic times, it is questionable whether the temples of Set and Nephthys (along with the settlement itself) were still occupied. Indeed, a derogatory reference to "Set of Sepermeru" on the walls of the Ptolemaic temple of Horus (at Edfu) notes that the town's canals were "dried up and forgotten" by the turn of the Common Era. This may have been a mere "hieroglyphic insult" rendered to Set, enemy of Horus, for the epithet "Set of Sepermeru" was still obviously familiar to the temple theologians. The capital of the 19th Nome had long before shifted to Oxyrhynchus in any case. Thus, it is likely that the settlement had waned considerably in significance.The history of the site, however, remains notable from an ancient Egyptian perspective because of the favor lavished by the Ramessid kings upon the temples of Nephthys and Set. Set's favor declined throughout Egypt with the downfall of these kings (except in the Delta and various northern oases), while Nephthys achieved greater popularity in her role as a goddess of the Osirian cycle, especially with temples of her own at Komir and Diospolis Parva (Hiw), where the entire 7th Upper Egyptian Nome was considered to be her particular "fiefdom" in Late Period and Greco-Roman times.

Sources:

A Ptolemaic Lexikon, Penelope Wilson (1997); The Goddesses of Pharaonic Egypt, Rene LaChaud (1992); Papyrus Wilbour (Berlin)

[edit] Takeshi Kimeda Sensei

Tekeshi Kimeda Sensei was born in Tokyo, Japan. In 1941, Kimeda Sensei has been a professional instructor of Yoshinkai Aikido in Canada for more than 35 years.

He began his study of Aikido under both Master Shioda and Kushida Sensei at 18 years of age while he was a university student. During his senior University years he was captain of the University Aikido Club. He graduated from University with a degree in Business Administration and a third degree black belt in Yoshinkai Aikido.

In 1964 Kimeda Sensei brought Yoshinkai Aikido to North America. He initially taught in California, then moved to Michigan where he opened the first Yoshinkai Dojo in Dearborn, Michigan. From Dearborn, he decided to come to Canada, opening the first Aikido school here.

Kimeda Sensei has developed many frontiers for Aikido outside Japan. He was instrumental in bringing Kushida Sensei and Karasawa Sensei to North America, also in inspiring many other instructors to teach outside Japan.

Kimeda Sensei is the chief instructor of Aikido Yoshinkai Canada, and holds the rank of 8th degree black belt. He currently has over 500 students in 15 dojos throughout Canada, and has trained more than 200 students to black belt.

[edit] Sources

I am a former student of Kimeda Sensei. I studied under him for 4 years. Factual information about him and his life can be found on many Aikido websites including www.aikido-world.com and www.aikidojournal.com Atom Cunningham 68.144.99.119 06:27, 20 May 2006 (UTC)

[edit] Burton "Bud" Koffman

Mr. Burton "Bud" Koffman is an incredibly secretive Jewish-American financier and businessman, who resides in the city of Binghamton, New York, as well as other locations around the world. Despite the fact that he is one of the wealthiest citizens in the United States, once owned the Sands Casino in Las Vegas as well as a myriad of Caribbean resorts, an industrial empire, exclusive contracts to distribute foreign cars in the U.S., and an investment bank, there is virtually no public information or knowledge of him. Finding information about him is difficult but not impossible, and the more that is uncovered the more interesting of a figure he seems to become.

[edit] [ [Penis Theory] ]

Penis Theory Abstract Penis theory is a branch of applied masculine studies that analyzes hypothetical (yet existing) relationships in unstructured courtship. Macro penis theory is a corrolary to the Buldge/income equation, in which male desirability is a function of independent variables-- penis size and income. Beginning in April 2006, Penis theory was initially developed as a tool for understanding seemingly irrational female behavior. Derived from non-experimental reasoning, Penis theory builds from several premises resultant from an implicit hierarchy of psycho-social observations: i. Women derive sexual gratification from larger penii. ii. Wealth is an essential component of longterm male/female interaction in western society iii. The sexual revolution has limited traditional societal norms iv. The pop-culture phenomenon of Sex and the City(see Whore studies)

Penis theory has been applied to other social science disciplines including: macro/micro cockeconomics, critical feminism, whore studies, and theoretical buldgenomics. It has drawn attention.

History Penis theory was developed by disillusioned University of California undergrads Allen Gilio and Dave Markman in April 2006.

notation--in the process of being developed. All concept/theories are not currently existing and are being created.

[edit] J-Lyriq

Detroit native J-LYRIQ is a gritty, urban contemporary/neo-soul singer, songwriter and self taught producer. His influences range from Sam Cooke, Donny Hathaway, and Marvin Gaye to Jodeci, Brian Mcknight, and R. Kelly. Like other R&B artist who have emerged in the '90s and 2000s, J-Lyriq looks to different eras for inspiration. The classic soul of the '60s and '70s impact his singing and producing, but so have the urban contemporary and hip-hop of the '80s, '90s and 2000s.

At times, J-Lyriq can be flat-out retro; some of his material would have been right at home on an old Motown LP from R&B's pre-'80s, pre-urban contemporary, pre-hip-hop era. Other times he has a more modern, hip-hop-influenced outlook. In other words, he has some songs that are quite friendly to urban radio, and others that would be too old-school for urban radio.His goal is to not be able to be compared to any other artist.

Born and raised in Detroit, Michigan, where he was the last of 8 children, J-Lyriq had a very musical upbringing -- one that included a steady diet of R&B and soul. When he wasn't performing gospel, J-Lyriq listened to secular soul and funk -- and his favorites included Sam Cooke, Otis Redding, Donny Hathaway, and the Gap Band. As a lead in his choir he had big dreams of worldwide fame.

[edit] Ioannis Amanatidis

Ioannis Amanatidis was born on the 3rd December, 1981 in Kozani, Greece. He is a Greek footballer, who has served as a full Greek international.

Amanatidis' early career in football was unconventional, yet promising . He began playing football in Kozani with his friends (rather than with a professional club) on the streets of the town. His first experience in organised football came at the age of nine, when he moved to Germany with his family. It was at SC Stuttgart that he first laced up his boots, demonstrating a devastating instinct for scoring goals even in his early years, and becoming the leading goalscorer during his four years with the Swabian club.

Amanatidis has, since then, played a large majority of his football in Germany, most notable are his performances with German clubs Kaiserslautern and, of course, Stuttgart. He currently plays for Eintracht Frankfurt, and serves as one of their key frontmen in the Frankfurt strikeforce. He played a vital role for Frankfurt in the 2005/2006 season, helping them stay in the German Bundesliga, and finishing the season as the clubs highest goalscorer for the year, with 12 goals. Amanatidis also led the way in the German cup, with Frankfurt just losing out to German champions Bayern Munich in the final. Amanatidis had a chance to be the hero of the night, having his 88th minute strike off a corner parried away by keeper Oliver Kahn.

Despite having such a promising career ahead of him at many periods of his blossoming career, unlike many notable Greek national players, Amanatidis was left out of the Greece squad which won the 2004 Euro Final. When asking coach Otto Rehagel why he was left out, he admitted:

"I asked Rehhagel before the European Championship why I had been left out. He explained and I accepted it".

He is no doubt, in the future, going to be in the plans for Greece, and despite Greece not making the World Cup in Germany, Amanatidis has a lot to look forward to internationally. Amanatidis was also named in the Greek squad that travels down under to meet Australia on Thursday 25th, 2006, in Melbourne.

[edit] "Sick" Nick Mondo

Born Matt Burns in Minneapolis, Minnesota. Nick Mondo quickly rose to fame in CZW (Combat Zone Wrestling) as one of its brightest stars. Making his debut in March of 1999, Nick Mondo's career, although short-lived was one of the most succesful of all those who competed in CZW. Despite giving up much in size and power to competitors such as John Zandig, Nate Hatred, The Wifebeater and Necro Butcher, Mondo was able to stand toe-to-toe with these competitors in the ring. Notable incidents from Mondo's Career include his fall of the top of the Warehouse in Delaware at Tournament of Death 2. During this 2 Out Of 3 Falls Light-Tube Log-Cabin Match. Mondo and his opponent John Zandig fell from the top of a warehouse through 4 tables and one of the Light-Tube Log-Cabins. This fall left Mondo's back badly lascerated, despite this he managed to win the match. Later that night he would also defeat Ian Rotten to win TOD2. Sadly only a few months after TOD 2 on November 10th 2003 Nick Mondo announced he was retiring due to Injury. In his four and a half year carreer Mondo had won The CZW Iron Man Title 3 times, the CZW Tag Titles with Ric Blade, the AWF championship and the NCWA Hardcore Championship, along with Tournament of Death 2. Other notable Mondo matches include Nick Mondo vs Homeless Jimmy from the original Tournament of Death, a TLC match at Cage of Death 4 between the team of Mondo and Ric Blade and The Backseat Boyz and Nick Mondo vs Nick Gage vs Nick Berk in a Tables, Ladders and Violence Match where Mondo won his 2nd CZW Iron Man belt.

[edit] Order of Prince Danilo I of Montenegro

The Order of Prince Danilo I of Montenegro was the first Montenegrin state Order and was established as a single class Order by His Royal Highness Prince Danilo Petrovic on St. George's Day April 23 (May 5), 1852, as the Order of Danilo I for the Independence of Montenegro “in order to honor the courage and the accomplishments of his subjects and of all those who dedicated themselves to defend the holy thing of the fatherland independence”. The Order became dormant upon the exile of the Royal House, though with living members and is still awarded to prominent champions of the preservation of Montenegrin independence. The conditions by which the Order is awarded are defined by Statute.

Alterations were made to the appearance of the original decoration created by Prince Danilo and during the rule of His Majesty King Nikola I Petrovic the Order underwent two restructures. During the first restructure on St. Goerge's Day April 23 (May 5), 1861, three classes were introduced, The King introducing two upper degrees, Grand Cross and Commander, with specific insignias; the old cross becoming a third class, Knight. On April 23 (May 5), 1873, the second reorganisation of the Order expands the field of rewards to civilian merits, establishes a Grand Chancellery and adds an intermediary class of Grand Officer between those of Grand Cross and Commander. In 1893, a third reform of the statutes establishes a fourth class, resulting from a reclassification of the existing class of Knight. The old cross then became a fifth class.

Throughout the history of the Order, the insignia has been produced by several famous medallists, the best-known being Arthus Bertrand, Beranger & Magdalaine (Paris, France), A. Chobillion (Paris, France), D. Cravanzola (Roma, Italy), R. Marschall (Vienna, Austria), Vincent Mayer (Vienna, Austria), C.F. Rothe & Neffe (Vienna, Austria), A. Ryabkov (St. Petersburg, Russia), G.A. Scheid (Vienna, Austria), Silberberg (Hamburg, Germany) and presently Thomas Fattorini (Birmingham, United Kingdom).

Many deserving men and women have been awarded the Order of Prince Danilo I over time including foreigners. The illustrious list includes many decorated servicemen during the World Wars and a host of other notables, including Queen Victoria and King Edward VII of Great Britain, as well as being written about by F. Scott Fitzgerald in 'The Great Gatsby'.

The Order of Prince Danilo I is the prerogative of the Head of the Royal House of Montenegro. On November 11, 2004 in Cetinje, His Majesty King Nikola II Petrovic Njegos, Hereditary Grand Master, reformed the Order, keeping the organisation of 1873 in five classes, but renaming them into Grand Cross, Knight Commander, Knight, Lieutenant and Member. The Grand Cross class is divided in four grades: Diamond Star, Gold Star, Silver Star and Grand Cross. The Hereditary Grand Master and the Grand Chancellor of the Order both wear an additional Collar of the Order.

The Order of Danilo I is registered in Montenegro as a Non-Governmental Organisation (NGO). Revised statutes of the Order were enacted on April 23 (May 5), 2005.

The present Hereditary Grand Master is His Majesty King Nikola II Petrovic Njegos of Montenegro. The Vice Grand Master is His Royal Highness Hereditary Prince Boris Petrovic Njegos of Montenegro, Grand Duke of Grahovo and Zeta. The Grand Chancellor of the Order is John Gvozdenovic, kinsman of the late General Anto Gvozdenovic (the last Grand Chancellor of the Order under King Nikola I).

The Successive Grand Masters since 1852 have been: His Majesty King Nikola II (from 24 March 1986); His Majesty King Michael (from 7 March 1921 to 24 March 1986); His Majesty King Danilo Alexander (from 1 March 1921 to 7 March 1921); His Majesty King Nikola I (from 13 August 1860 to 1 March 1921), and; Sovereign Prince Danilo I (from 23 April/5 June 1852 to 13 August 1860).

Glenn Dellimore Glenn Dellimore, born 1972 in London, England, privately educated in London and holder of various England athletic records, gained entry to the London Royal College of Design and graduated from London Barons Court College in Leisure & Entertainment Business Management.

Dellimore founded a national U.K health club events company, designing membership events for the Lord Sebastian Coe health clubs brand. Thereafter, Dellimore designed and founded a renowned ‘five star’ luxury health club in London.

As Dellimore advanced in the entertainment world, he moved from London to Beverly Hills. Liaising with major Hollywood film studios, Dellimore developed two international talent entertainment businesses. Dellimore’s Celeb Entertainment is an international talent booking company for the world’s most popular international talent attending U.K appearances with CelebEvents, formerly known as Jealous Events.

Appearances booked by Jealous Events include Kelly Donovan and Stacey Scowley for a Buffy the Vampire Slayer and Angel convention. Kelly Donovan was a stunt double for the show, and Stacey Scowley was an extra in one episode.

Glenn Dellimore was featured on the U.K television BBC consumer complaints programme Watchdog in 2003 regarding the Jealous Events David Boreanaz Event. Many attendees were not satisfaid with this event due to the lack of organisation. Fans were left out-of-pocket, in some cases for hundreds of pounds, regarding refunds that were promised and never delivered. Glenn Dellimore's name is well known on the U.K convention circuit as an organiser who's events most do not wish to attend.

Glenn Dellimore is back on the U.K convention scene as CelebEvents. Many people believe the name change from Jealous Events to CelebEvents is to mask the 'bad reputation' he now has, so new attendees will be unaware of the hundreds of fans left out-of-pocket from his previous events.

[edit] Peanut Test

The peanut test can be used to see if you are (in)compatible with someone in terms of a relationship.

The test was originated in the UK and hence uses the main British flavours in nuts. It can be expanded to other nations' tipples but must be kept concise for clarity and maximum effect.

The test is as follows:

Which type of peanut do you prefer?

a) Dry Roasted b) Salted c) I don't like peanuts

The answer must be one of the above. Such comments as "well I don't really mind" are not permitted.

[edit] Order of Saint Peter of Cetinje

The Order of Saint Peter of Cetinje was the first dynastic Order of the Royal House of Montenegro and was introduced by His Majesty King Nikola I Petrovic in 1869. It is sometimes said that this order was actually introduced much earlier by Prince-Bishop (Vladica) Peter II Petrovic-Njegoš. The Order is bestowed upon prominent members of the Royal House, the Petrovic-Njegoš family, as well as to prominent foreign citizens, and is currently held by all members of the Royal House.

The name of Prince Danilo, the first Montenegrin ruler with a purely secular title, is inscribed on the Decoration. The Order was named after the Patron Saint of the Montenegrin Orthodox Church, Prince-Bishop (Vladika) Peter I Petrovic, the person who effectively obtained independence for Montenegro, and to whom is attributed the creation of the modern Montengrin State.

Tzar Alexander II of Russia was the first recipient of the Order, awarded on June 29, 1871. During his reign, King Nikola I never organised the Order and maintained it as a single class Dynastic Order, rewarding only members of the Montenegrin Royal Family and related such as Alexander I of Serbia (1888-1934), King Petar I of Serbia (1844-1921), Ljubica “Zorka” Petrovic Njegos (1864-1890), Duke Ilija Plamenac (1821-1917), Duke Bozo Petrovic Njegos (1846-1929), King Vittorio Emanuele III of Italy (1869-1947), and Jelena Petrovic Njegos (1873-1952) etc.

The present Grand Master is His Majesty King Nikola II and the Grand Chancellor is John Gvozdenovic.

The Order consists of a single class, and is normally reserved for members of the Royal Family and their kinsmen and in exceptional circumstances prominent foreign citizens.

Current living recipients include: Her Majesty Queen France, His Royal Highness Hereditary Prince Boris, Grand Duke of Grahovo and Zeta, Her Royal Highness Princess Altinai, His Most Eminent Highness Fra' Andrew Bertie, Prince and Grand Master of the Sovereign Order of Malta, His Highness Prince Nicholas of Russia, His Serence Highness Prince Dimitri of Russia, His Royal Highness Vittorio Emanuele of Savoy, Prince of Naples, Her Royal Highness Marina of Savoy, Princess of Naples, His Royal Highness Emanuele Filiberto of Savoy, Prince of Venice and John Gvozdenovic.

[edit] Sources

http://www.orderofdanilo.org/ The Official Website of the Royal House Orders of Montenegro

[edit] Feel the Darkness

Feel the Darkness is the most famous album by the punk band Poison Idea. Widely regarded as one of the best punk albums of all time, it has gained worldwide critical acclaim. Songs on the album have been covered by everyone from Pantera to Machine Head (as a bonus track on their Burn My Eyes album). It was originally released in 1990, and was reissued in 2004 by Golf records

[edit] Dj Steve Dee

DJ Steve Dee is one of the most influential DJ's of our time and the creator of the "The Funk" known to the world as "Beat Juggling" one of the greatest things to hit deejaying, since the Scratch. "Beat Juggling" is the act of manipulating individual drum beats, or vocal phrases, in order to create a unique composition using multiple turntables. Steve Dee was the founding member of the original DJ group "The X-Men" (later know as the X-Ecutioners) and fathered the movement called "Turntablism." Dj Steve Dee has worked with artist like Dougie Fresh & the Get Fresh Crew, the ever controversial Luther ‘Luke Skywalker aka Uncle Luke’ Campbell, Wreckx n Effect, Japanese superstar Toshi Kubota, Teddy Riley’s “Guy & BlackStreet”, and worked on international megastar Michael Jackson's "Dangerous" album. In 2000 DJ Steve Dee was inducted into the "DMC DJ HALL of FAME" for his immense contribution to the world of deejaying. He is also the last DJ to win the New Music Seminar Battle for World Supremacy. He can be seen in the DJ documentary "Scratch" or you can check him out at [12].

[edit] AFL Best Player

In each year of its ten-year existence (1960 - 1969), numerous sports-news services named their choice for the American Football League's best first-year player. The choices by the major services are shown below.


[edit] 1961

[edit] (UPI, TSN)

EARL FAISON, defensive end, San Diego Chargers

Despite being double and triple-teamed, Faison was chosen as the AFL Rookie of the Year in 1961. The 6-foot-5, 260-pound Earl Faison blew by opposing offensive lineman on his way to smashing American Football League quarterbacks as one of the original "Fearsome Foursome", and was chosen to the AFL All-Star team in 1961.


[edit] 1962

[edit] (UPI, TSN)

CURTIS McCLINTON, fullback, Dallas Texans

McClinton had 604 Yards on 111 carries for a 5.4 yards per carry average and two touchdowns. He added 333 yards on 29 receptions and was a member of the 1962 AFL All-Star team.

[edit] 1963

[edit] (UPI, TSN)

BILLY JOE, fullback, Denver Broncos

An eleventh-round draft choice by the Broncos, Joe had 646 yards on 154 carries for a 4.2 yards per carry average, four rushing touchdowns, and a reception for a touchdown.


[edit] 1964

[edit] (UPI, TSN)

MATT SNELL, fullback, New York Jets

Selected in the third round in the NFL draft, Matt Snell was picked in the first round as the first player drafted by the AFL's New York franchise after new owner Sonny Werblin changed the team's name from the Titans of New York. Snell rolled up 948 yards on 215 carries, for a 4.4 yards per carry average, with an additional 393 yards on 56 receptions, with four touchdowns rushing and one receiving. He was also named to the 1964 AFL All-Star team.


[edit] 1965

[edit] (UPI, TSN)

JOE NAMATH, quarterbackback, New York Jets

Choosing the American Football League's Jets (and $427,000) over the NFL, Namath was 164 of 340 for 2,220 yards and 18 touchdowns in his rookie season for the Jets, and was selected to the 1965 AFL All-Star team.


[edit] 1966

[edit] (UPI, TSN)

BOBBY BURNETT, halfback, Buffalo Bills

Arkansas' Bobby Burnett had a combined total of 1,185 yards rushing and receiving at the halfback position, with over 12 yards per catch and 4 toucdowns on 34 receptions, and 766 yards on 187 rushes, with 4 rushing touchdowns. He was also selected to the 1966 AFL All-Star team.


[edit] 1967

[edit] (UPI)

GEORGE WEBSTER, linebacker, Houston Oilers

George Webster created the "roverback" position, as a linebacker with a defensive back's moves and speed. He started as a rookie and had 15 tackles in his first game. The Oilers' defense held opponents under 200 points in 1967, helping them win the East Division title. He averaged more than ten tackles a game and was first-team All-AFL in 1967.


[edit] (TSN)

DICKIE POST, halfback, San Diego Chargers

Dickie Post rushed for 691 yards and 7 touchdowns on 161 carries in 1967, and caught 32 passes with the Chargers for 278 yards and a touchdown. He made the AFL All-Star team in 1967 and would make it again in 1969.


[edit] 1968

[edit] (UPI, TSN)

PAUL ROBINSON, halfback, Cincinnati Bengals

Paul Robinson played only one year at the University of Arizona, but in his first year as a professional, he gained 1,023 yards rushing and scored eight touchdowns. He was named to the 1968 All-AFL team and led the Western AFL All-Star team to victory over the Eastern All-Stars.


[edit] 1969

[edit] (UPI)

GREG COOK, quarterback, Cincinnati Bengals

The University of Cincinnati's 6-foot-4, 220-pound quarterback Greg Cook stayed in Cincinnati to play professional football. In his rookie year, he passed for 1,854 yards and 15 touchdowns. Injury prevented him from reaching his potential with the Bengals.


[edit] (TSN)

CARL GARRETT, halfback, Boston Patriots

Carl Garrett caught 29 passes for 267 yards and two touchdowns in 1969, and ran the ball for over five yards per carry with 137 attempts for 691 yards and five touchdowns. He was also selected to the AFL All-Star team in 1969.

[edit] George W. Bush in popular culture

George W. Bush has been satirically depicted in various media throughout the years, often in a negative context. Listed below are all the films, comics, websites, songs, tv series who've parodied or criticised him at least once:

[edit] Comics

  • In the work of cartoonist Ted Rall he is often depicted as a dictator
  • In the last Asterix album Asterix and the Falling Sky the leader of the Toon aliens is called "Hubs" an anagram of Bush.

[edit] Songs

In this list also songs about the war in Iraq are included, because they often criticize the war or war as a phenomenon in particular, however when these songs take a neutral point of view they are listed a little lower.

  • "American Idiot" (Green Day)
  • "An Open Letter To NYC" (The Beastie Boys)
  • "Bomb The World" (Spearhead)
  • "Dear Mr. President" (P!nk)
  • "Doofpot" (Osdorp Posse)
  • "Hail To The Thief" (Radiohead) (the title is a pun on the song Hail To The Chief and references the rumor that Bush stole the 2000 US presidential elections)
  • "Mosh" (Eminem)
  • "Wake Me Up When September Ends" (Green Day)
  • "Weg Met Amerika" (Raymond van het Groenewoud). The title of this Flemish album (in English: "Down with America") caused a small stream of criticism against the anti-American title.

[edit] Songs about the war in Iraq without mentioning Bush

Some of these songs happen to be about war even without specifically talking about the war in Iraq. However, it must be said that so many songs about peace and against war have appeared during Bush's presidency that all of them, even if not a real criticism against the Bush administration must of could have been inspired by the wars in Afghanistan and Iraq.

  • "The Day After Tommorow" -(Tom Waits)
  • "How To Dismantle An Atomic Bomb" - (U2)
  • "Weapon Of Mass Destruction" (Faithless)

[edit] Music Videos

  • Rage Against The Machine's music video Testify for the US presidential elections of 2000 showed Bush and Al Gore as a sort of aliens who talk and act the same. The clip also makes use of archive footage and at one point an image of two girls kissing each other is followed by film footage of Bush looking very frightened.
  • In Madonna 's video for her single American Life (2003) she was originally shown in army outfit while leading troops of female soldiers. At the end of the clip she throws a hand grenade at a lookalike of Bush who then lights it with a cigar. It received so much criticism that Madonna replaced the clip with less controversial images.
  • In George Michael's video for Shoot The Dog (2002) the animation, provided by the British animated series 2DTV, shows Bush and Tony Blair at one point firing missiles at Saddam Hussein. Blair is shown as a pet and admiring, almost homosexual assistent to a very childlike Bush.
  • Green Day's clip for Wake Me Up When Tommorow Comes (2004) shows a girl bursting in tears when she finds out her boyfriend is going to fight in Iraq. The video shows him as a soldier who is eventually shot in a desert like setting.
  • Eminem's clip for Mosh is an animation of Eminem and various people who gather together to march to a building out of protest against Bush. During the animated clip real life filmed material is shown of Bush during a presidential speech. In the end of the clip Eminem and the stream of people are shown registering to vote against Bush. After the 2004 elections however a different ending was shown: Eminem arrives at the building where Bush is seen, giving a speech. When he sees Eminem he hides behind his desk.

[edit] Tv series

  • In the British animation series 2DTV Bush is often depicted as an infantile person.
  • Trey Parker and Matt Stone of South Park fame once made a sitcom about president Bush: That's My Bush. It featured lookalikes of him, Laura Bush and his administration and was set in The White House. The series were more a satire on American sitcoms than on Bush's presidency.
  • In the British satirical series Dead Ringers Bush's dyslexia is mocked whenever he is imitated.

[edit] Errata sheet

An errata sheet is a common method of post-production editing in which the errors left in the produced copy are outlined on a sheet of paper bound into the book. This is a common method by which large works are "edited"; i.e. if the volume would cost too much and/or be too incongruous to edit, this is an acceptable method by which one might edit the work.

It should be noted that errata sheets should only outline minor errors within a work (e.g. misspellings, improper punctuation and the like). If a major error in the construction of a sentence occurs, or if the construction is such that the idea that the sentence delivers is unclear or distorted to the point of confusion or the delivery of the wrong idea, this MUST be corrected within the work.

[edit] Sources

Webster's Third International Dictionary (Unabridged)

24.153.205.144 13:28, 20 May 2006 (UTC)

[edit] Discussion

  • Article created as a part of Erratum; redirected thence. Sandstein 12:28, 21 May 2006 (UTC)

[edit] Champlin Creek

Champlin Creek is located between the hamlets of Islip and East Islip, flowing southward into the Great South Bay.The fish and wildlife habitat is an approximate three and one-half mile length of the stream, extending from Knapps Lake, just north of the Main Street, to near its headwaters north of the Southern State Parkway. Champlin Creek is a relatively clean, cold, free-flowing, freshwater stream, generally less than 6 feet wide, partially vegetated sandy substrate. The creek is bordered by limited areas of wet forest land and suburban residential development. Champlin Creek is one of only a few free-flowing, spring-fed streams on Long Island that have remained in a relatively natural state. This creek provides habitat conditions suitable for natural reproduction by brook trout, and supports one of approximately 6 known wild populations of this species on Long Island. In addition to the native fish populations in Champlin Creek, brown trout and rainbow trout are stocked in the stream by the NYSDEC, provide a recreational fishery of county-level significance. Public access for fishing the area is available along the east side of Knapps Lake and at road crossings.

[edit] West Burton

Once captured in a Turner painting, the unknown honeypot West Burton is a small but quite interestiing village in North Yorkshire. Situated in Wensleydale, one of the infamous Yorkshire Dales, it is a place of beauty and relaxation. It has a traditional inn which is focal point for local tourism in the area. it has few residents but has wonderful housing and accommodation. The village's main attraction is undoubtedly the splendid beauty and enchantment of the Cauldron Falls, secretly nestled away by three large guest houses. The three cottages are perfectly suited to the areas countryside atmsophere and are the pecfect veiwing point for the natarul beauty beside them. The village also has a local shop which provides everything you are likely to need. the shop is joined on to craft shop which contains entertainment and interest in one little building. it also has room for a lovely little pottery shop and on the green, a small antiques shop full of ancient delights. All together this village is a place of beauty, enchantment, exitement, fun, interest, entertainment and overall enjoyment. an extra treat for residents of the area is the mobile chip van that visits the villge every wednesday night at about 8pm. Come and have a look for yourself. West Burton is also just one mile away from the National Park Centre in Aysgarth, with equally splendid beauty and another snapshot of natural beauty in Aysgarth Falls.

[edit] In These Arms

In These Arms was the third single to be released from rock band Bon Jovi's fifth studio album, Keep the Faith. It reached 27 on the US Hot 100 and was a Top Ten hit in Australia and the UK.

In These Arms was co-written by Bon Jovi keyboardist David Bryan, It also appears on his solo album, Lunar Eclipse.

Although a firm fan favourite, it is widely regarded to be under-rated, perhaps due to it's release after that of Keep the Faith (which achieved Number 1 on the US Main Stream Rock Tracks) and Bed of Roses.

It is currently being played on Bon Jovi's current 'Have a Nice' Day tour.
